Ad Text:
Company description:



SCHOTT is a leading international technology group in the areas of specialty glass and glass-ceramics. With more than 130 years of outstanding development, materials and technology expertise we offer a broad portfolio of high-quality products and intelligent solutions. SCHOTT is an innovative enabler for many industries, including the home appliance, pharmaceutical, electronics, optics, life sciences, automotive and aviation industries. SCHOTT strives to play an important part of everyone's life and is committed to innovation and sustainable success. The parent company, SCHOTT AG, has its headquarters in Mainz (Germany) and is solely owned by the Carl Zeiss Foundation. As a foundation company, SCHOTT assumes special responsibility for its employees, society and the environment.

SCHOTT MINIFAB is a leading provider of microfluidic diagnostic consumables, driving innovation at the intersection of science, engineering, and healthcare. As part of the global SCHOTT Group, we belong to the Strategic Business Field Diagnostics, working alongside two other specialised sites in Phoenix (US) and Jena (Germany) to deliver cutting-edge solutions that make a real difference in people's lives.

Our Melbourne site plays a key role in this mission, offering a dynamic, purpose-driven environment where your work directly contributes to the future of life sciences and diagnostics.



Job description:

About us

SCHOTT MINIFAB is a leading provider of microfluidic diagnostic consumables, driving innovation at the intersection of science, engineering, and healthcare. As part of the global SCHOTT Group, we belong to the Strategic Business Field Diagnostics, working alongside two other specialised sites in Phoenix (US) and Jena (Germany) to deliver cutting-edge solutions that make a real difference in people's lives.

Our Melbourne site plays a key role in this mission, offering a dynamic, purpose-driven environment where your work directly contributes to the future of life sciences and diagnostics.

Kick-start your career in a dynamic, hands-on environment where you'll work alongside experienced experts to design and support innovative automation and custom tooling solutions that enable scalable, repeatable manufacturing processes.

In this associate role for recent graduates (Please note: this opportunity is a fixed-term contract of up to one year), you'll gain valuable experience turning user requirements into standardized, modular systems, and play a key part in installation, validation, and long-term maintainability—all while learning and growing in a collaborative team setting.

Your Contribution
Apply standardized approaches to cell layout, HMIs, and controls architecture to ensure modularity and design consistency
Assist in designing high-volume automation applications and low-volume, batch-oriented assembly tools
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to help draft User Requirement Specifications (URS) and translate them into compliant system designs
Support equipment fabrication, assembly, and debugging in hands-on development settings
Help plan and execute Factory Acceptance Testing (FAT) and Site Acceptance Testing (SAT) for automated systems
Assist in training engineering teams on system use, troubleshooting, and maintenance
Support project delivery teams by contributing to automation workstream scope, quality, and technical deliverables within program budgets
Your Profile
Bachelor's degree in Engineering (Automation, Electrical, Mechatronics, Control Systems, Computer Engineering) or equivalent
1-2 years of post-graduate experience as an Automation Engineer or in a similar role with special-purpose machines, jigs, fixtures or robotics
Ability to conceptualise and implement innovative system design solutions for production environments
Ideally experienced in HMI and PLC programming
Familiar with GMP standards and ISO 13485 (desirable)
Strong technical aptitude with a genuine passion for automation and a self-starter mindset
Team player with excellent communication skills and a strong willingness to learn
Your Benefits

SCHOTT's openness to promote your further development is just as great as our additional benefits. Ranging from active health management via a supportive and inclusive work environment, and a strong team spirit with regular social events, all the way to corporate development programs and training: everything geared to suit your goals and needs. Discover a special corporate culture where everyone has the opportunity to develop their entire potential.

At SCHOTT, you can expect a unique corporate culture where we emphasize equity, diversity, and inclusion. We know: motivated and committed employees are the precondition for the success of our company.

Please feel free to contact us

You can expect interesting tasks and challenging projects, as well as motivated and friendly teams in fields that influence our future. Do you want to be successful with us? Then, please send us your application: SCHOTT MiniFAB Pty Ltd, Human Resources, Kristina Lemme2

Salary: Good salary + bonus + lots of chocolate
Ad Text:
Are You Ready to Make It Happen at Mondelēz International?

Join our Mission to Lead the Future of Snacking. Make It With Pride.

Mondelēz International empowers people to snack right in over 150 countries around the world. We're leading the future of snacking with iconic global and local brands such as Oreo, Cadbury, Philadelphia, Pascall, The Natural Confectionery Company, Belvita, Ritz and Toblerone with global revenues exceeding $31 billion USD.

Claremont is the largest Cadbury factory in Australia and Southern Hemisphere. Recently celebrating 100 years in production, the site delivers 200 million blocks, and 60,000 tonnes of chocolate annually, including other iconic products like Cadbury Freddo, Twirl and Caramello Koala to name a few!

You plan, develop and execute capital projects by supporting technical developments, feasibility perspectives of engineering-related activities in supply chain and capital expense project execution to support growth, world-class manufacturing and productivity with the highest levels of quality, safety and environmental requirements. You will follow Mondelēz business and innovation processes in project management and ensure that Mondelēz standards are adhered to.




How you will contribute

Reporting into the Capital Engineering Manager of our iconic Cadbury Plant in Claremont, Tasmania, the role of the Senior Automation Engineer is to lead and execute capital projects at the Claremont Manufacturing site, ensuring the successful implementation of automation upgrades, expansions, and new installations.

The Senior Automation Engineer ensures that all projects are managed to the highest standards of safety, quality, and compliance, ensuring that relevant technical standards are met.  This role involves the full project lifecycle, from initial planning and budgeting through to installation, commissioning, and ongoing support. This role will advise and support other capital engineering team members on electrical & automation decisions within other projects.

The Senior Automation Engineer will collaborate and liaise with respective Reliability Engineers and Operational team members in order to meet project, maintenance and operational needs.




What you will bring

A desire to drive your future and accelerate your career. You will bring experience and knowledge in:

·       Technical expertise across engineering disciplines and high expertise in one or more domains an advantage and these relevant skills include, Industrial Networking & Cybersecurity, Industrial Control Systems (ICS), Regulatory Compliance (Safety, Security, Environmental), Electrical Power Systems, Quality Management & Food Safety, Process Knowledge (Food Manufacturing), Manufacturing Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) and most importantly Project Management Principles.

·       10+ years industry experience, experience working within food industry preferred

·       Lean manufacturing / Continuous Improvement (eg. TPS)

·       Significant Project engineering and Management experience

·       Leading to work effectively across cross-functional teams and influencing key stakeholders

·       Experience with people management, leadership and development

·       Strong communication (written and verbal skills)

·       Strategic Prioritisation

·       Problem Solving

·       AutoCAD and MS office suite proficiency

·       SAP proficiency is highly desired




Additional Job Description

An engineering degree recognised by the Engineers Australia Institute is required to be considered for this position, and current Work Rights.







Business Unit Summary

At Mondelez International, our mission is to provide consumers with the right snack, for the right moment, made in the right way. We are one of the largest snack companies in the world, with global net revenues exceeding $31 billion USD.

We have operations in more than 80 countries and employ approximately 91,000 diverse and talented employees in our factories, offices, research & development facilities and distribution activities around the world.

In Australia and New Zealand, we have 6 factories, and both global and local brands, employing over 2,000 people; Cadbury Dairy Milk, Oreo, Toblerone, Philadelphia, belVita, Pascall, The Natural Confectionery Company, Sour Patch Kids and Ritz.

Mondelēz International is an equal opportunity employer and all qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation or preference, gender identity, national origin, disability status, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law.

Job Title: Data Engineer- 12 month Max Term Contract
Ad Text:
About Ticketek Entertainment Group​

Ticketek Entertainment Group is a global fan experience Company that tickets, promotes and delivers incredible live experiences that are impossible to forget.  In a distracted world where nothing beats real human moments, We make life better live!

Our Group includes; our Fan Experience Platform (Ticketek) that sells tickets and provides value added services, Event promoting with businesses across Touring (TEG Touring), Sport (TEG Sport), and Family Experiences (TEG Experiences) and our digital business (Ovation) which focuses on delivering seamless data-driven outcomes for our fans and partners

About the Role: 

We are seeking a Data Engineer to harness data-driven solutions within our Technology team. This is your chance to apply your strong coding expertise and industry best practices to architect and implement the crucial data pipelines that power strategic business outcomes. You will be instrumental in transforming raw data, managing large-scale integration projects, setting up streaming services, and implementing Machine Learning (ML) models into production, making a direct impact on fan experiences.



Requirements



What does a day in the life look like?

Ensure adherence to data privacy, security, observability, and governance standards.
Collaborate with architects and senior engineers to design resilient, high-performance data solutions.
Build scalable data pipelines to ingest, process, and expose data using technologies like Snowflake, AWS Redshift, Kinesis, Lambda, DynamoDB, S3, Glue, Apache Storm, and others.
Develop batch and streaming data solutions using Apache Kafka, Apache Spark, Airflow, and Delta Lake for real-time and scheduled data processing.
Automate ingestion from external sources, ensuring reliability and data quality.
Design and implement event-driven data architectures with streaming frameworks such as Kafka Streams and Kinesis Data Firehose.
Implement Data Quality, Data Lineage, and Observability frameworks
Collaborate with Site Reliability Engineers to ensure stability and uptime of production pipelines and services.
Work with Data Scientists to ensure high-quality data for Machine Learning models and integrate them into production-ready pipelines.
Stay up-to-date and continuously upskill on emerging technologies, frameworks, and best practices in data engineering and cloud platforms.

About You 

Essential experience & skills

Undergraduate degree focused on Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science or a related discipline.
3+ years of hands-on experience in data profiling, ETL development, SQL optimization, and testing.
Proven experience delivering large-scale data solutions with AWS technologies (Kinesis, Athena, Redshift, DynamoDB, Lambda, S3).
Proficiency with modern data platforms and tools, including Snowflake, Databricks, and Apache Storm.
3+ years of experience working with SQL and NoSQL databases, particularly MongoDB.
Familiarity with CI/CD tools and practices like Ansible, CloudFormation, and Jenkins.
Strong ability to translate complex business requirements into technical data solutions.
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to collaborate effectively with both technical and non-technical teams.

Desirable experience & skills

Jira / Confluence experience
Experience consuming RET
Experience to AI/ML technologies.


Benefits



Here’s a taste of what TEG offers: 

Complimentary event tickets
Birthday and volunteering leave
Wellbeing discounts & flu vaccinations
Paid parental leave & free employee support (EAP)
Global rewards and recognition
Learning, development & career pathways
A diverse, inclusive, and passionate team

Equal Opportunities

TEG is an equal opportunity employer committed to embrace diversity, respect, and care for our people and communities. 

If there are any adjustments that need to be made to ensure you have a fair and equitable experience in our recruitment process, please advise us when scheduling your interview. 

*Only direct applications will be considered. No recruiters please*

About Us
At UniSuper, we're committed to delivering great retirement outcomes for our members. As one of Australia's largest superannuation funds, we're proud of our inclusive, high-performing culture and our focus on innovation and excellence. Our Data Office is at the heart of our digital transformation, enabling strategic decision-making and member value through data-driven insights.

The Role
Are you ready to shape the future of data at UniSuper? As a Staff Data Engineer, you'll be a senior technical leader within our Data Engineering team, responsible for delivering enterprise-scale data solutions that underpin our strategic objectives. You'll play a pivotal role in enabling analytics, ML/AI, and operational data pipelines, while championing engineering best practices and mentoring other data engineers.

You will:


Provide technical leadership across multiple portfolio projects, ensuring data engineering solutions align with business outcomes and architectural standards.
Be hands-on in designing, developing, and delivering scalable, secure, and high-performance data pipelines and architectures (batch and real-time) using Azure Databricks, PySpark, DBT, and Fivetran.
Drive platform evolution by introducing innovative solutions, frameworks, and accelerators that improve delivery speed, quality, and cost efficiency.
Champion best practices in data engineering, including CI/CD, infrastructure-as-code (Terraform), data quality, and governance.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams (Data Governance, Risk, Data Science, Cloud Infrastructure, and Solution Architecture) to deliver integrated, compliant, and business-focused data solutions.
Mentor and coach senior and mid-level engineers, fostering a culture of technical excellence, continuous learning, and knowledge sharing.
Lead complex problem-solving for performance optimisation, scalability, and reliability of data pipelines and platform components.
Ensure alignment of data engineering initiatives with UniSuper's Enterprise Data Platform strategy and contribute to long-term architectural roadmaps.
Represent Data Engineering in portfolio planning and delivery forums, providing expert advice on data architecture, design patterns, and delivery approaches.
About You
You are a seasoned data engineering professional with a proven track record of delivering enterprise-grade data solutions and leading technical teams in complex environments. You bring:


10+ years of experience in data engineering, with at least 2+ years in a senior or staff-level leadership role.
Deep expertise in Azure cloud services, Databricks, Delta Lake, and Medallion architecture.
Strong proficiency in PySpark, DBT, and modern ETL/ELT tools (e.g., Fivetran, Azure Data Factory).
Demonstrated experience in real-time and batch data processing, streaming technologies (e.g., Kafka), and data integration from diverse sources.
Advanced knowledge of infrastructure automation (Terraform) and CI/CD pipelines using Azure DevOps or similar tools.
Strong understanding of data governance, security, and compliance in cloud environments.
Ability to lead by example, being hands-on in designing, developing, and delivering high-quality data solutions while guiding others.
Proven ability to influence and guide technical direction across multiple projects and stakeholders, balancing innovation with business priorities.
Exceptional problem-solving skills, with the ability to troubleshoot complex data and infrastructure issues.
A passion for mentoring and developing talent, fostering a collaborative and high-performing engineering culture.
Excellent communication skills to engage with technical and non-technical stakeholders at all levels.
Why UniSuper?
We offer a supportive and inclusive environment where you can thrive and make a real impact. Enjoy a competitive salary, generous superannuation, flexible working arrangements, and a range of benefits designed to support your wellbeing and professional growth. At UniSuper, we value diversity and encourage applications from all backgrounds. Even if you don't meet every requirement, we'd love to hear from you.

About I-MED Radiology Network

I-MED is a global leader and ANZ's largest, privately owned radiology network. The work we do every day is at the core of providing quality medical imaging services to patients across our 270 clinics. When you work for I-MED you form part of a critical supply chain that supports emergency departments, obstetrics, oncology clinics and we deliver over 6.5 Million patient procedures annually.  

Backed by global private equity, today we are a $1.2B business with additional joint venture partnerships, that includes a global leader in Artificial Intelligence technology for Radiology.  

About the Role

As a Cloud Engineer, you will play a critical role in designing, implementing, and maintaining secure and scalable cloud networking solutions that support our medical imaging services. You'll work closely with platform, infrastructure, and operations teams to optimise cloud connectivity, enforce robust security protocols, and ensure high availability across our environments. Your expertise will help safeguard sensitive healthcare data, streamline network performance, and enable agile service delivery across the organisation.

What You'll Be Doing

Designing and maintaining AWS cloud networking, including VPCs, subnets, routing, DNS (Route 53), and hybrid connectivity (Direct Connect, TGW, megaport)
Act as third-level support for cloud network-related issues, working closely with IT Network Operations and internal stakeholders
Building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines to automate build, test, and deployment processes using GitLab CI/CD
Implementing and monitoring cloud networking and security controls to enhance visibility, detect threats, and support automated response
Investigating, responding to, and documenting cloud security and networking incidents, including root cause analysis and remediation
Conducting risk assessments and ensuring compliance with frameworks such as OWASP, NIST, and Essential 8
Standardising and enhancing IT solutions, processes, and documentation to improve operations and governance
Sharing technical knowledge, mentoring team members, and contributing to cross-functional projects as a technical expert

 

What We're Looking For

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field (or equivalent experience)
AWS certifications such as Solutions Architect Associate and Advanced Networking Specialty (or equivalent)
Strong expertise in AWS cloud services with a focus on networking, hybrid connectivity, security best practices, and automation
Hands-on experience with DevOps tools (GitLab CI/CD), Infrastructure as Code (Terraform), and scripting/programming (Bash, Python, PowerShell)
In-depth knowledge of networking concepts, VPC, IAM, firewalls, VPNs, IDS/IPS, and security controls
Familiarity with ITIL practices, particularly Change Enablement, Incident Management, and Knowledge Management
Strong problem-solving, analytical, and troubleshooting skills with a customer-focused mindset
Proven ability to collaborate across teams, communicate effectively, and mentor/upskill others
Proactive approach to continuous learning, innovation, and professional development

 

What We Offer

Comprehensive training and continuous professional development
A supportive, innovative, and purpose-driven work environment
Health and wellbeing programs including EAP and staff benefits
Career growth opportunities across a national network
The chance to contribute to impactful technology projects that save lives

If you're passionate about cloud technology and want to be part of a team driving innovation in healthcare, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply today and help us deliver outstanding medical imaging services through cutting-edge cloud infrastructure.

Sydney (Hybrid)

Join our data engineering team as a Data Engineer, where you’ll play a key role in developing, maintaining, and optimising modern data pipelines. You’ll work hands-on with tools such as dbt, Airflow, Snowflake, and Databricks, building scalable data solutions that enable analytics and product insights across the business.

In this role, you’ll contribute to the design of data models, drive improvements in data quality and performance, and collaborate with stakeholders to deliver reliable, well-documented solutions. It’s an exciting opportunity for a mid-level engineer who wants to deepen their expertise in cloud data platforms while making a meaningful impact in a growing data team.

Job Description


Data Engineering & Pipeline Development

Design, build, and maintain scalable data pipelines using modern data stack tools (dbt, Airflow, Python).
Take ownership of troubleshooting and resolving issues in data workflows, ensuring reliable and timely data delivery.
Work with Databricks and Snowflake environments to support ingestion, transformation, and modelling of data.
Contribute to development and optimisation of Unity Catalog, Delta Live Tables, and Spark within Databricks.

Data Modelling & Solution Design
